#note in hindsight, I like dropping TURN on this turn. leaving 3 in the bag limits the range of plays Mina can make (although dropping an L play at 1M is going to be a great option for her, often). Also there are two Ts and a U left in the bag, so WORN has serious duplication risks. with all that said, I don't see how NRW is going to win after Mina scores next turn (again, she can just fish at 1M most of the time), so I'm ok with trying this.
>Mina: DEU C2 .UED +20 392
>JD: AINRTUY 11H YUAN +26 402
#note really interesting and tough pre-endgame! I'm in bad shape here. Mina can win most of the time just by dropping EYE at 11D. There are two ways I can counter: one is by blocking the spot with UNITY at 12A. That's the only way I can win on paper - when I draw the Y, I end up with two great outs (YURTA and ARTY at 3F), and steal a 2-point win! She also has to play perfectly if the D or the E are in the bag. I did not consider options like this enough over the board because I didn't think they'd score enough. Option #2 is to punish her for dropping EYE by holding back scoring tiles and trying to outrun. To do that, I can play ULAN at 1L keeping the Y. If she plays EYE immediately, I can steal a win if the A or L were in the bag, and she has to play a perfect out-in-two to beat an E draw. My play of YUAN ties if I draw the A and is somewhat threatening if I draw the E, but these other two plays would've given me a better shot.
